tIceNLP is an open source Natural Language Processing (NLP) toolkit for analysing and processing Icelandic text.

http://sourceforge.net/projects/icenlp

-----------------------------------------
The project is checked out with: 
svn co https://icenlp.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/icenlp icenlp

This file contains information about the contents of the subdirectory core.

The core includes core utilities like a tokeniser, a unknown word guesser, a PoS tagger, a finite state parser, a lemmatiser, and a Named Entity Recogniser.

Various files are automatically generated (and thus not part of the svn).
The following steps are needed to generated these files for the first time:

	 cd flex/icetagger
	./compileRules.sh

	cd flex/iceparser
	./flexAll.sh

	cd flex/iceparser/errorSearch
	./flexAll.sh

	cd flex/iceNER
	./flexit.sh

	cd dict/lemmald
	./makeRules.sh

	cd doc
	./maketex.sh

Then the core can be compiled with:
ant
